{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "De Fauw et al.",
    "trained a CNN on 14,884 OCT scans and achieved an AUC of 0.99 for detecting referable AMD, with a sensitivity of 96.6% and a specificity of 99.0% (17).",
    "The model's performance was comparable to that of retinal specialists, suggesting that AI could replace human graders in AMD screening.",
    "Similarly, Treder et al.",
    "developed a CNN model that achieved an accuracy of 96.7% in classifying OCT images as usual or AMD, demonstrating the potential of AI to enhance the efficiency of AMD screening (18)."
  ],
